sentences: Denis Matthews (27 February 1919 – 25 December 1988) was an English pianist and musicologist.
He attended Arnold Lodge School, Leamington Spa, from 1927 to 1932 and Warwick School from October 1932 to the summer of 1936, when he left to study at the Royal Academy of Music.
In the few years before his death, he and his third wife, Beryl Chempin, taught at the Birmingham School of Music.
